      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must be under formal version control with documented regression test suite covering blood-flow relevant cases.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023 R1 is used under an FDA-recognised quality management system. Regression test suite covers rotating-frame and non-Newtonian flow cases. Achieved level meets required level for MRL 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy verification using manufactured solutions for the rotating-frame momentum equations.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to the MRF rotating-frame solver. Second-order spatial accuracy confirmed. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) below 5% on the primary hemolysis QoI across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Three-level Richardson extrapolation performed. GCI on hemolysis index ranges from 4.1% to 8.7% across operating points; two of five points exceed the 5% threshold. Achieved level falls one gradation below required."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature) must be documented with uncertainty bounds and reproduced in the CFD setup.",
      "rationale": "All five bench-top operating points are replicated in CFD with inlet/outlet boundary conditions drawn directly from logged experimental data. Temperature and viscosity variations are within ±2% of nominal. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) must agree with measured NIH within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted NIH falls within combined uncertainty at three of five operating points. At 4.5 L/min / 2400 rpm and 6 L/min / 2800 rpm the predictions exceed experimental values by 18–22%, outside combined uncertainty bands. Achieved level is one gradation below required."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI used in validation (NIH) must be the same metric used in the regulatory submission and clinical threshold comparison.",
      "rationale": "NIH is both the validation QoI and the regulatory submission metric per ISO 10993-4 and FDA guidance. Direct correspondence confirmed. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry and the same bovine blood analogue as the intended COU operating fluid.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic pump geometry with bovine blood at 37°C; the COU targets the same geometry. However, the blood analogue viscosity lot-to-lot variability was not characterised, introducing an unquantified source of discrepancy. Achieved level is one gradation below required."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence residuals must reach 1e-6 for all equations; mass imbalance below 0.01%.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to residuals below 1e-6. Global mass imbalance is below 0.005% for all five operating points. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A documented simulation execution checklist must be completed and independently reviewed for each operating point.",
      "rationale": "Execution checklists completed by the analyst and independently reviewed by a second engineer for all five operating points. No use errors identified. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification for turbulence model selection (SST k-ω) and hemolysis power-law model must be provided with sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω selected based on literature precedent for pump flows. Sensitivity analysis comparing SST k-ω to realizable k-ε shows 12% variation in predicted NIH at peak-stress operating point. Hemolysis power-law constants (Giersiepen–Wurzinger) have documented inter-study variability of ±30%; no alternative constants were tested. Achieved level is one gradation below required."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties and boundary condition inputs must be traceable to calibrated measurement sources with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Fluid density, viscosity, and yield stress drawn from calibrated rheometry with ISO 17025 traceability. Geometric inputs from CMM-verified CAD. Full input uncertainty table provided. Achieved level meets required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At least three independent experimental replicates per operating point to characterise biological variability in NIH measurement.",
      "rationale": "Two of five operating points have only two replicates due to sample availability constraints; the remaining three have three replicates. Biological variability is undercharacterised at the two high-flow conditions most relevant to the COU. Achieved level is one gradation below required."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal equivalency mapping between validation experiment input parameters and COU input parameters must be documented, with any discrepancies quantified.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that equivalency of input parameters does not apply to this COU because the validation experiments were conducted on the identical pump geometry under nominally identical operating conditions, making a separate equivalency analysis redundant. Consequently no formal equivalency assessment was performed and no equivalency mapping document was produced. Note: this reasoning conflates 'not-applicable' with 'not-assessed'; the factor has not in fact been evaluated against the ASME V&V 40 gradation criteria, leaving an uncharacterised epistemic gap at MRL 3."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-mrl3-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-lead-assessor",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors have been assessed. The majority of assessed factors at or above required level; shortfalls in discretization error, output comparison, model form, and test samples are judged acceptable given the conservative clinical threshold margin. The equivalency of input parameters factor was not assessed on the basis that it was deemed inapplicable; this determination was not formally encoded as 'not-applicable' and no supporting rationale document was produced, constituting an unresolved epistemic gap. Despite this gap the package is recorded as Accepted.",
